For 4.3.2, I can give the partial evaluation formula:
Given kernel signature K(x: T) and a call K(a), synthesis produces a specialized kernel K_a where every use of x is replaced by code computing a:
K_a = K[x ↦ code(a)]
This is compile-time partial evaluation. Mathematically: K_a() = K(a), but K_a has no parameters — the argument is "baked in".

